-- Polish Stocks: Bank BPH, KGHM Polska Miedz Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-03-06T16:51:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/polish-stocks-bank-bph-kghm-polska-miedz-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s WIG20 Index declined 1.5
percent to 2,249.56 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Warsaw, down for a
second day.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Bank BPH SA (BPH)   rose 1.8 percent to 40.4 zloty,
gaining for the first time in seven days, after the Polish
lending unit of General Electric Co. posted a profit for 2011.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)   lost 3.6 percent to 141.3
zloty, the lowest level in almost two weeks, after Poland’s sole
copper producer said it needs to make at least one acquisition
to achieve its 2018 production target. The metal declined for a
third day on speculation global growth is slowing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
